,0.079648,0.087882,0.094569,0.094888,0.096829,0.097558,0.097193,0.092196,0.078283]},{"section":19,"text":"So the diagnosis would be HBeAg-negative chronic hepatitis B.","dimension":7,"group":0,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.028708,0.055801,0.064322,0.070807,0.077178,0.082694,0.087944,0.090795,0.095273,0.096486,0.10373,0.14626],"unified_progress":[0.028713,0.042807,0.052317,0.060996,0.066085,0.07807,0.080664,0.091492,0.1003,0.10403,0.12981,0.16472]},{"section":20,"text":"Alternatively, maybe it's an immune flare in chronic hepatitis B. Alternatively, could it be acute hepatitis B?","dimension":0,"group":6,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.028238,0.055887,0.066258,0.075207,0.085877,0.091968,0.097888,0.10371,0.10488,0.10471,0.09996,0.085414],"unified_progress":[0.035864,0.057151,0.071492,0.082042,0.087358,0.091725,0.096874,0.10136,0.10253,0.10142,0.093643,0.078553]},{"section":21,"text":"But HBeAg negative and anti-HBe positive usually takes time to develop, so acute is less likely.","dimension":1,"group":4,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.027823,0.060155,0.073089,0.082028,0.089807,0.096167,0.10055,0.10167,0.10073,0.098288,0.092311,0.077383],"unified_progress":[0.056755,0.072629,0.079035,0.082967,0.089523,0.092455,0.093346,0.097022,0.094292,0.092409,0.0829,0.066667]},{"section":22,"text":"The key points are chronic infection (HBsAg + for over 6 months, but we don't know the duration here).","dimension":11,"group":5,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.033316,0.066833,0.0765,0.083059,0.089311,0.096416,0.09678,0.09774,0.096174,0.094635,0.08873,0.080506],"unified_progress":[0.061718,0.088362,0.085528,0.085849,0.086989,0.089832,0.08847,0.090873,0.086714,0.085078,0.079755,0.070832]},{"section":23,"text":"But given the seroconversion from HBeAg to anti-HBe, that's a sign of chronic infection.","dimension":2,"group":7,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.03748,0.070357,0.078934,0.085712,0.090816,0.095376,0.096462,0.095421,0.093888,0.09142